The paper deals with strategic games and their rationality, which falls under the category of game theory (cs.GT). The use of first-order and modal fixpoint languages suggests a logical approach, which could place the paper in the category of logic in computer science (cs.LO). The paper also discusses the concept of belief, which is a key aspect of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of fixpoints and iterated elimination of non-optimal strategies suggests a connection to multi-agent systems (cs.MA). Finally, the paper deals with the analysis of strategies, which could place it in the category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
